    <note>Sang(1) Zhuang [18169] Lu You, WJ, 33.2b-3b (wife, born Lu, who died in 1185 at age 74). His wife's great grandfather can be positively identified as Gui based on highest office and posthumous title. Zhuang is identified in CBD, as a husband of You's sister, but the titles of the unnamed grandfather and father of born Lu do not correspond to those of You's father and grandfather. Zhuang's father, a minor official, fled the military disturbances of the Jianyan period (1127-30) and found himself in Tiantai where born Lu's father was county zhubu. Since the two families had already had a history of "continuous intermarriage [liangjia yi ji hunyin)," the marriage was arranged. She was buried in Tiantai, new home of this branch of the Gaoyou Sang. Chicheng zhi, 34.22b. CBD, 3, 1847.</note>
